<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="912" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d912">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 417.00/54.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-26"><hi rend="italic">July 26,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The Department agrees to postponement of modifications of decree as
                            outlined in Department’s June 26, in accordance with your July 20.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>